      "writtenOn": "2020-11-25T06:56:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I am not sure if I agree on this:\n1. This is not a usual behavior. If I were the user, I would expect the option persist.\n2. If a user switch to the legacy page, it is likely that the new page is not as useful for them. In such cases, I suspect some more proactive approaches (like showing them a panel asking what\u0027s wrong, or reaching out to them directly), will provide us more information about what went wrong than silently switching them to the new page again.",
