      "writtenOn": "2020-11-26T04:21:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "True, that\u0027s a good idea.\n\nMy reasoning for suggesting this is that it effectively gives users a nudge back to the new page every month. Since we\u0027ll probably be turning off the old page in, say, 4 months time, that\u0027s only a few nudges. We could also consider a longer time period, like 2 months.\n\nThe other reason is that it\u0027d be nice to have the cookie not sitting around forever. If we\u0027re not going to use cookie expiry as a nudge mechanism, how about a 1-year expiry?",
      "parentUuid": "04f38cd5_c53a79c3",
